...Excuse me, I was intruding. (This tavern has a dangerous
smell to it after all. I better leave.)

This is the most troublesome spot in the village. Hurry up
and leave. You don't want to have another scary experience,
do you?

The wicked residents of this village were mistaken for
bandits and got caught by the officials. Because of that,
the tavern's sales have dropped, but well, it might have
been for the best for the village.

Five years ago, Mount Fuji had a massive eruption. This
village was relatively unscathed, so people from nearby who
couldn't find food started flocking here. As a result, it's
now become the most dangerous village in the Kanto region.

Defeating those bandits is quite impressive. Honestly, they
were a thorn in our side, so it feels refreshing. Ah, the
sake tastes great!
【Drunkard】

Hehe... booze tastes great when you drink it in the
afternoon... Miss, you're quite the beauty... Pour me
another one. And how about a little blowjob too, eh?♪
Kekeke!
【Drunkard】

Let's have a drink to celebrate the bandits being caught...♪
*hic*...

I've seen the head of those bandits once, and that ain't no
human... Wielding a ridiculously huge sword with ease.
That's just impossible...

I've heard rumors that a group resembling demons has
appeared in Atami as well. They seem to be calling
themselves the Oni Ontou. It's quite dangerous indeed.

...It's better for your own good not to talk to those men
over there. They're rough types with bad drinking habits.
Just know that the bald guy with the headband is part of a
bandit gang.

It's good that the captured girls have been freed. This
should help restore some peace to the village.

If you don't want to be deceived, you'd better leave this
tavern quickly. Otherwise, you'll have a terrible time,
hehehe!

This place is a haven for us ruffians. Even if you're a
young girl, I won't let it slide if you make a fuss, got it?
*hic*...

Your body was damn good. All the men here are now brothers
by the same hole. Kah kah kah!
(It's so frustrating... but... it makes me angry...)

...You've walked around town, you've noticed, haven't you?
This village has fewer decent humans. It's a terrifying
place where you might even get your ass drilled while
soaking in the hot springs.
We're just drunkards, not bandits... *hic*...

I was invited to become a bandit, but I didn't fancy going
bald. Well, drinking from noon suits me better... Boss,
another round!

Cheers to the delightful annihilation of the bandits! Gulp
gulp--!

Kah kah kah! This Sunuramu Village is our bandit territory!
We won't show mercy, even if you're an official!
